latestIgtvVideos.title: How I Use My Revlon One Step Dryer
latestIgtvVideos.caption: I’ve been using the Revlon One Step Dryer for a couple of years and have always had great success with it! In February, I decided to give the Dyson Airwrap a shot and retired my Revlon Dryer for over 9 months until I decided it was much more compatible for my hair than the Dyson. Overall, if you’re someone who wants a fast and effective volumized blow out, you can’t go wrong with the Revlon One Step! Unfortunately, I just don’t feel the Dyson has long lasting results for hair that has any amount of curl, texture or frizz. It wasn’t a time saver for me and I always felt underwhelmed by the results. If you’re interested in seeing a tutorial using the Dyson, I posted one here on my IGTV several months ago! Otherwise, this is my fool proof routine with the One Step! My hair stays smooth and volumized for 3-4 days!

latestIgtvVideos.title: KNC Supa Scrub + Collagen Lip Mask
latestIgtvVideos.caption: I pledged to invest more of my social promotions and money into black owned beauty brands. @kncbeauty was one of the first that caught my eye (I mean look at those lip masks 👄) The lip scrub is DIVINE and leaves your lips extremely soft. I’ve always avoided lip scrubs because I’ve felt they leave my lips dryer - this formula does the complete opposite. The lip masks are such a fun addition. The entire lower portion of my face immediately felt soothed and hydrated after removing the mask. They also make masks for your under eye area and a lip balm (I’m a dumb dumb and thought the scrub set I ordered came with one lol will be ordering ASAP though) 💗❤️
